The paper proposes a divide-and-conquer algorithm for large scale kernel learning with application to clustering. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The algorithm also involves compression and random projections, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) research. Additionally, the paper mentions parallel multicore or clustered computation, which is relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
